cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.MM

This paper deals with analyzing data from online social networks (OSNs) to extract public opinion on movies. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also introduces new metrics to compare the opinion of Twitter users with that of the online population of IMDb and Rotten Tomatoes, which falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses the potential of such data to predict a movie's box-office success, which could be categorized under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper analyzes the characteristics of Twitter users and their preferences, which falls under the sub-category cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences).
